  "text": "It has been hypothesized that metabolically 'quiet' human and mammalian embryos have better developmental potential [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . There was no significant difference between net amino acid production between different embryo groups, but embryos cryopreserved on Day 2 which subsequently lost cells upon thawing and underwent developmental arrest during Days 2-3 had consistently and significantly (P , 0.05) higher net amino acid consumption, net amino acid activity and net turnover than any other tissue group.",
